title: Nürnberger Vereinigungsparteitag
subtitle: The formal unification of the <span style="color: [+ uspd_colour +];">**USPD**</span> with our <span style="color: [+ spd_colour +];">**SPD**</span>
new-page: true
max-visits: 1
view-if: uspd_joining_proces == 1
on-arrival: unemployed_uspd -= 3
tags: event
face-image: img/unnamed (1).jpg

= Nürmberger Vereinigungsparteitag

Otto Wels wants this to go smoothly, it is a largely symbolical congress...

- @make_uspd_concessions: We will make some concessions to the <span style="color: [+ uspd_colour +];">**USPD**</span> showing that this a unification, not an annexation.
- @ignore_concession: They have no choice, so why should we make any concession to traitors.
- @skip_vspd: We will actually not do this.

@make_uspd_concessions

What will we offer them

- @lowest_uspd: Let at least one former <span style="color: [+ uspd_colour +];">**USPD**</span> member into each important section of the executive commitee.
- @middle_uspd: The above and, eventually, a new party programme.
- @good_uspd: The above and a new party leadership
- @high_uspd: The above and no coalitions with the <span style="color: [+ dvp_colour +];">**DVP**</span>.
- @highest_uspd: The above and no coalitions with any of the bourgeois parties.
- @no_uspd: Ok, we won't make concessions.

@lowest_uspd
on-arrival: spd_party_leader_3 = "Crispien"; spd_party_leader_n += 1

Former <span style="color: [+ uspd_colour +];">**USPD**</span> leader Arthur Crispien will become our third chairman alongside Hermann Müller and Otto Wels.

<span style="color: #AFAFAF;">**Drop an advisor to be replaced with Crispien.**</span>

- @drop_ebert: Drop Ebert (reformist)
- @drop_scheidemann: Drop Scheidemann (centrist)
- @drop_wels: Drop Wels (centrist)
- @drop_muller: Drop Müller (centrist)

@drop_ebert
on-arrival: ebert_advisor = 0; crispien_advisor = 1; reformist_strength -= 5; center_strength_ += 5; left_dissent -= 5
go-to: new_swap

Ebert doesnt care much about party affairs. 

@drop_scheidemann
on-arrival: scheidemann_advisor = 0; crispien_advisor = 1
go-to: new_swap

Scheidemann is old anyways.

@drop_wels
on-arrival: wels_advisor = 0; crispien_advisor = 1
go-to: new_swap

Wels doesn't judge.

@drop_muller
on-arrival: muller_advisor = 0; crispien_advisor = 1
go-to: new_swap

Müller is more useful as a chancelor...

@middle_uspd
on-arrival: new_party_programm += 1
go-to: lowest_uspd

A new party programme is surely logical.

@good_uspd
subtitle: The <span style="color: [+ uspd_colour +];">**USPD**</span> will be pleased by this.
unavailable-subtitle: Hermann Müller and Otto Wels are already a pivot to our center.
choose-if: left_strength >= 10
on-arrival: spd_party_leader_2 = "Breitscheid"; reformist_dissent += 3; not_bad_vspd_deal = 1
go-to: lowest_uspd

Our new leadership election has decided on the ousting of Hermann Müller in favour of Rudolf Breitscheid, a pragmatic, yet principaled internationalist socialist democrat. Otto Wels on the other hand remains firm in his position.

@high_uspd
unavailable-subtitle: We will likely need to work with them at some point.
subtitle: Working with the <span style="color: [+ dvp_colour +];">**DVP**</span> is already unpoplular with our proper base.
view-if: left_strength >= 10
choose-if: left_strength > reformist_strength
on-arrival: good_uspd_vspd_deal = 1
go-to: lowest_uspd

We don't know how this will end...

@highest_uspd
subtitle: The reformists are outraged!
view-if: left_strength >= 20
choose-if: left_strength >= 40 and left_strength > reformist_strength
unavailable-subtitle: The <span style="color: [+ uspd_colour +];">**USPD**</span> has actually agreed to work with the <span style="color: [+ z_colour +];">**Center**</span> by now.
on-arrival: second_kpd_essentially = 1; reformist_dissent += 25
go-to: lowest_uspd

The <span style="color: [+ spd_colour +];">**SPD**</span> will dedicate itself to the proletarian revolution!

@no_uspd
go-to: ignore_concession

@ignore_concession

The <span style="color: [+ uspd_colour +];">**USPD**</span> is outraged.

- @make_uspd_concessions: Ok, we will make some concessions...
- @eat_it_uspd: What are they gonna do?

@eat_it_uspd
on-arrival: reformist_strength += 10; left_dissent += 15; uspd_joined = 1; unemployed_spd -= 3; z_relation += 2; unemployed_uspd -= 15; unemployed_kpd += 13; workers_uspd -= 4; worker_spd += 1; uspd_relation -= 55; spd_r = old_spd_r + uspd_r*0.81; uspd_r = uspd_r*0.19

The former <span style="color: [+ uspd_colour +];">**USPD**</span> members in our party are outraged about the treatment they are greated with. Some less convinced members like <span style="color: #700000;">**Kurt Rosenfeld**</span> or <span style="color: #700000;">**Georg Ledebour**</span> reject joining us as they don't see any future in the <span style="color: [+ spd_colour +];">**SPD**</span>. Yet despite the treatment they've received many members join our ranks seeing the <span style="color: [+ spd_colour +];">**SPD**</span> as their only future. 

The <span style="color: [+ kpd_colour +];">**KPD**</span> profits a lot.

@ new_swap

[? if spd_party_leader_2 == "Müller": <span style="color: #AFAFAF;">**you can swap another advisor for Rudolf Breitscheid**</span> ?]

