@low_vspd
view-if: new_party_programm == 0 and good_uspd_vspd_deal == 0 and second_kpd_essentially == 0
on-arrival: uspd_relation -= 45; unemployed_uspd -= 13; unemployed_kpd += 11; workers_spd += 2; workers_uspd -= 4; spd_r = old_spd_r + uspd_r*0.9; uspd_r = uspd_r*0.1; uspd_joined = 2; thuringia_gov = "SPD"; saxony_gov = "SPD"; uspd_leader = "Ledebour"; uspd_ideology = "Spartacism"; sender_in = "SPD"; siemsen_in = "SPD"; breitscheid_in = "SPD"; aufhauser_in = "SPD"; crispien_in = "SPD"; hilferding_in = "SPD"; kautsky_in = "SPD"

Our new <span style="color: #c00000;">**VSPD**</span> is signed into existance. Everyone knows it is more a continuation of the <span style="color: #c00000;">**MSPD**</span> than the <span style="color: #AA0000;">**USPD**</span> but most can arrannge themselves with the state of how things are.

Many <span style="color: #D47B9B;">**USPD**</span> members are reluctant to join but see no other alternatives. A lot join the <span style="color: #700000;">**KPD**</span> instead with only a tiny rest remaining in the "Rest-<span style="color: #D47B9B;">**USPD**</span>".

@middle_vspd
view-if: new_party_programm == 1 and good_uspd_vspd_deal == 0 and second_kpd_essentially == 0
