@high_vspd
view-if: good_uspd_vspd_deal == 1
on-arrival: coalition_dissent += 1; unemployed_spd += 2; old_middle_spd -= 3; new_middle_spd -= 3*(1-dissent); left_dissent -= 15; reformist_dissent += 25; kpd_relation += 10; left_strength += 20; new_party_programm += 1; center_relation -= 8; ddp_relation -= 5; dvp_relation -= 15; uspd_joined = 2; uspd_relation += 5; unemployed_uspd -= 15; unemployed_kpd += 2; unemployed_spd += 14; spd_r = old_spd_r + uspd_r*0.95; uspd_r = uspd_r*0.05; workers_spd = workers_spd + workers_uspd*0.9; workers_uspd = workers_uspd*0.1; unemployed_spd = unemployed_spd + unemployed_uspd*0.9; unemployed_uspd -= 4; catholics_spd = catholics_spd + catholics_uspd; catholics_uspd = 0; thuringia_gov = "SPD"; saxony_gov = "SPD"; uspd_leader = "Ledebour"; uspd_ideology = "Spartacism"; rosenfeld_in = "SPD"; levi_in = "SPD"; sender_in = "SPD"; siemsen_in = "SPD"; breitscheid_in = "SPD"; aufhauser_in = "SPD"; crispien_in = "SPD"; hilferding_in = "SPD"; kautsky_in = "SPD"

Our new <span style="color: #c00000;">**VSPD**</span> is signed into existance. It seems it is more of a continuation of the <span style="color: #D47B9B;">**USPD**</span> than the <span style="color: #c00000;">**MSPD**</span>. Let's hope it will survive longer than the last one.

Many reformist members are displeased about this change. A few <span style="color: #D47B9B;">**USPD**</span> members join the <span style="color: #700000;">**KPD**</span> instead with only a tiny rest remaining in the "Rest-<span style="color: #D47B9B;">**USPD**</span>" that won't believe our new course.

We hope for the best.

@kpd_without_moscow
view-if: second_kpd_essentially == 1
on-arrival: coalition_dissent += 5; unemployed_spd += 5; new_middle_spd -= 3*(1-dissent); old_middle_spd -= 5; left_dissent -= 55; reformist_dissent += 45; kpd_relation += 25; left_strength += 25; new_party_programm += 1; center_relation -= 20; ddp_relation -= 15; dvp_relation -= 45; uspd_joined = 3; spd_r = old_spd_r + uspd_r; uspd_r = 0; unemployed_spd = unemployed_spd + unemployed_uspd; unemployed_uspd = 0; catholics_spd = catholics_spd + catholics_uspd; catholics_uspd = 0; new_middle_spd = new_middle_spd + new_middle_uspd; thuringia_gov = "SPD"; saxony_gov = "SPD"; uspd_leader = "gone"; ledebour_in = "SPD"; liebknecht_in = "SPD"; rosenfeld_in = "SPD"; levi_in = "SPD"; sender_in = "SPD"; siemsen_in = "SPD"; breitscheid_in = "SPD"; aufhauser_in = "SPD"; crispien_in = "SPD"; hilferding_in = "SPD"; kautsky_in = "SPD"

Even the most radical members like Georg Ledebour have agreed to the merger!

Our new <span style="color: #c00000;">**VSPD**</span> is signed into existance. Somehow it seems more left-wing than the initial <span style="color: #D47B9B;">**USPD**</span>. This turns the <span style="color: #c00000;">**SPD**</span> into a big tent party again.

We have yet to see; whether we can sustain that this time...

@skip_vspd
on-arrival: reformist_dissent -= 3; uspd_relation -= 55; unemployed_kpd += 10; unemployed_uspd -= 5; left_dissent += 5; kpd_relation -= 10; spd_r = old_spd_r + uspd_r*0.2; uspd_r = uspd_r*0.8

We have angered the <span style="color: #D47B9B;">**USPD**</span>...

Still some of their more centrist Reichstag delegates join us for some reason. Mostly because they wanted to jump off the sinking ship.
